(7, '1667136260296x695775423295914000', '', '', '', 'What are the Benefits of No-Code and Low-Code Tools?', 'Speed\nIt takes less time to produce the product. Even if a developer has to change the code, it’s faster than writing it from scratch. It reduces the project duration from years to months or even several weeks.\n\nCost-Effectiveness\nWith no-code/low-code technologies, you don’t rely fully on the specialists whose work usually costs a fortune. These instruments demand fewer resources. It results in lower costs of production and better ROI.\n\nArchitecture Consistency\nNo-code/low-code tools contribute to maintaining code and design consistency. Thus, developers may start fixing the bugs at once rather than spend time analyzing the software framework.\n\nQuick Response from the Clients\nNo-code/low-code instruments are ideal for building an MVP to check if the product is in demand. It will save not only your time but also resources and effort.\n', 'Oct 30, 2022 3:24 pm', 'Nov 4, 2022 4:51 pm'),
(8, '1667139627309x759430682376405000', '', '', '', 'No Code', 'As  its name suggests, is a type of app development that does not involve coding. Thus, it is accessible for casual app creators, so-called citizen developers. Anyone who wants to have a functional digital product through an easygoing process. \n\nMany research agencies predict the NoCode dominance by 2024. Every company wants to have a faster way to make a functioning, self-sustaining digital product. NoCode helps with that. \n\nAdditionally, finding and hiring high-quality software developers has become a challenge for companies. IT requires more automation, that''s why more and more businesses turn to NoCode. \n\nIf these are not enough advantages for you, the revenue numbers are impressive. By 2030, the NoCode development market will generate more than $150 billion.\n\n2021 is the year of NoCode. App development overcomes past challenges. By creating more powerful, varied, professional toolkits. ', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:20 pm', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:27 pm'),
(9, '1667139698791x268588321972682750', '', 'no', '', 'Take a look at Bubble, for example.', 'Through their fluid system you, whether coder or casual user, can come up with a functional application. By clicking and dragging the elements, connecting data, and choosing the slickest design sets to your taste. Their platform is becoming more secure, diverse, and collaborative each year. User-friendly layouts and dynamic content for mobile devices. Adaptive web and hybrid mobile applications. Connection to external services and hardware through APIs. Moreover, Bubble pushes their ecosystem, providing a self-sufficient platform. Without involving extra tools and\\or coding professionals! \n\n\nSwiftle takes this even further, revolutionise the market. They combine both NoCode and LowCode techniques. And offer an easy-to-use subscription service and brilliant final products.\n\nThere are a couple of features that make NoCode so vital in app development right now. The key to the 2021 success of NoCode was and continues to be integration. As much integration with everything. It helps to build a strong asset of tools on a platform. Also, it promotes your system among the users and fans of integrated services.  ', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:21 pm', 'Dec 3, 2022 8:06 pm'),
(10, '1667140058964x404521410814017540', '', '', '', 'The No Code platforms become more collaborative than before.', 'Now, they feature coherent team tools and interactions. Each company member could get the necessary insight. As well as take part in the decision-making on the final product. \n\nThese and other features help NoCode based projects skyrocket in growth: \n\nLambda School is an educational platform that helps you learn to program free of charge with a 17% installment payment after you get hired. They are currently valued at more than $150 million. \nFreelancer recruiting website Comet is made exclusively through Bubble. It allows companies to find the best freelancers on the market. Comet raised more than $10 million through investments in 2018.\nDividend Finance helps users to simplify their loan application process. They raised over $300 million through various funding sources.\n\nIn the future, the NoCode development will become the expected choice. By 2023, there will be more than 500 million new apps that cannot rely exclusively on coders. The toolkits are improving fast! And the NoCode platforms continue to diversify without being too complicated! Their efficiency is on another level. With collaborative, responsive, varied, integrative systems that can help anyone. Even your least tech-related employees! Now, they can build a functional, user-friendly application that will solve a client’s problem or need.  \nNoCode lets you create anything, no matter how proficient and complex the app project is. Next year looks bright: $28 billion in comparison with 2017''s $4 billion. ', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:27 pm', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:28 pm'),
(11, '1667140089691x677031441169645600', '', '', '', 'Why No Code is the future?', 'Cloud storage, total customization, cheaper infrastructure, fewer complexities like backlogs. No Code is the way for companies to achieve the best possible results in a short period of time with fewer resources. ', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:28 pm', 'Oct 30, 2022 4:28 pm'),
