(66, '1671450183889x820132242502975500', '', '', '', 'A Niche Startup vs a Huge Monster: What are the Chances?', 'Let’s consider the following example. Everyone knows such a company as Airbnb. With the help of this service, one can rent various types of housing – from comfortable cottages to luxurious penthouses. This service is known worldwide, as it’s available in different countries.\nOn the one hand, it may seem that this giant monster has taken over the entire rental market. There is no point in competing with Airbnb. Will any rental service be popular at the market? Are risks worth taking?\nAirbnb is huge and as versatile as possible. It can’t adapt to any niche, especially to so-called narrow requests. Let’s say you are looking for a room to hold a conference. Airbnb can’t help you with finding a place for a photo shoot or a meeting room. In this case, it’s better to go to [url=https://squares.kz/][color=#0285FF]the marketplace[/color][/url] that deals with commercial space.\nWith Squares, you can rent a venue for different events in 15 cities in Kazakhstan. Yes, it’s local but it has become successful in the Kazakh market because of its niche.', 'Dec 19, 2022 1:43 pm', 'Dec 19, 2022 1:46 pm'),
(67, '1671450355170x510978188961382400', '', '', '', 'What Does No-Code Have to Do With This?', 'The mentioned marketplace was developed, using no-code instruments. The advantages of creating a marketplace with no code are obvious:\n\n[color=#808080][size=4]It’s faster to launch the product.[/size][/color]\n\nCreating any marketplace from scratch takes a lot of time. Squares was ready in less than 2 months. \n\n[color=#808080][size=4]It’s easier to create an MVP.[/size][/color]\n\nBefore investing a huge sum of money into the product, it’s advisable to test if the product is competitive. With Squares, the MVP was more than successful. It encouraged the company to keep moving forward.\n\n[color=#808080][size=4]It’s possible to customize your product.[/size][/color]\n\nNo-code tools allow building a marketplace and customizing it according to your specifications. When you are looking for an appropriate commercial place, you have certain requirements. The selection criteria there are completely different from the ones you have when you search for housing. Thus, they need to be filtered differently. Not the way Airbnb filters its listings. \nNo-code platforms have all the features to create the product you need. \n\n[color=#808080][size=4]You always have an opportunity to scale.[/size][/color]\n\nThe company started with booking venues in one city. After the successful MVP launch, they added more cities. Now it’s possible to rent a venue in 15 cities in Kazakhstan. What is more, Squares is a marketplace for renting space for events with various loyalty systems integrations.\n\nSo, as you can see, niche startups do have the opportunity to become competitive and take their places in the market. If you have an idea for such a startup and still hesitate about whether it’s worth implementing, contact the Swiftle team. We will help to find a proper solution!\n\nIf you still have some doubts, our experts are waiting for your [url=https://calendly.com/swiftle/swiftle_demo][color=#0285FF]call[/color][/url].', 'Dec 19, 2022 1:45 pm', 'Dec 19, 2022 1:51 pm'),
(68, '1672230281196x805677084652339200', '', '', '', '', 'Today we will discuss how NoCode and ChatGPT can be used together to create chatbots that are able to understand and respond to customer inquiries and requests without the need for human intervention. We will also explore the various ways in which chatbots can be used to improve customer service and streamline business operations, as well as the benefits of using NoCode and ChatGPT together.', 'Dec 28, 2022 2:24 pm', 'Dec 28, 2022 2:28 pm'),
